00:42:44,897 --> 00:42:46,619
And we wanted a DLC that could make press.

977
00:42:46,779 --> 00:42:48,321
Like, that was very crazy and where people were like,

978
00:42:48,441 --> 00:42:50,964
oh, wow, like, if you release it a couple of months

979
00:42:51,044 --> 00:42:51,865
after the game, they were like,

980
00:42:51,946 --> 00:42:53,547
oh, I'm going to get back into Shadow Tactics.

981
00:42:53,588 --> 00:42:54,549
They have the moon, right?

982
00:42:55,610 --> 00:42:56,811
That was sort of the idea behind it.

983
00:42:57,923 --> 00:43:00,305
And you can see it's very janky with the performance.

984
00:43:01,546 --> 00:43:04,128
Then we had some ideas like what can you do in space?

985
00:43:04,709 --> 00:43:07,411
We reversed gravity so you can only jump upwards

986
00:43:08,052 --> 00:43:09,593
and have to take ladders to go down.

987
00:43:09,693 --> 00:43:10,634
This was very bad.

988
00:43:11,294 --> 00:43:14,177
We cut that from the, like we made two versions of this map

989
00:43:14,217 --> 00:43:15,498
and we cut that in the second one

990
00:43:15,538 --> 00:43:16,779
because it just wasn't intuitive

991
00:43:16,819 --> 00:43:18,020
and it felt completely stupid.

992
00:43:18,640 --> 00:43:20,342
And then we have like drones flying around.

993
00:43:20,382 --> 00:43:21,963
You can see here making light.

994
00:43:21,983 --> 00:43:23,224
So there was some cool stuff going on.

995
00:43:24,289 --> 00:43:26,511
This is by the way, we had all the assets built for this,

996
00:43:26,611 --> 00:43:27,652
they just weren't textured.

997
00:43:28,073 --> 00:43:30,315
There's a lot of game designer, level designer art in this.

998
00:43:30,876 --> 00:43:33,859
So in the center we have this huge shield

999
00:43:33,899 --> 00:43:37,522
and there's this crane thing that they're using

1000
00:43:37,582 --> 00:43:39,384
to sort of laser the face of the Shogun.

1001
00:43:39,945 --> 00:43:41,646
You're basically in one of his eyeballs.

1002
00:43:42,307 --> 00:43:43,768
This is the huge crater that you're in.

1003
00:43:46,055 --> 00:43:47,175
You could kill him in two ways.

1004
00:43:47,295 --> 00:43:49,216
Either you could kill him by sort of luring him

1005
00:43:49,496 --> 00:43:51,717
beneath this laser and killing him there,

1006
00:43:51,757 --> 00:43:54,378
or you could go over there and kill him using drop pods

1007
00:43:54,398 --> 00:43:55,238
that you could call down,

1008
00:43:55,298 --> 00:43:57,599
and the alarm guards would come and drop pods.

1009
00:43:57,619 --> 00:43:59,080
There's a lot of cool stuff.

1010
00:43:59,100 --> 00:44:02,181
You can see I'm a bit sad that we didn't get to do this.

1011
00:44:02,881 --> 00:44:05,162
Yeah, just wanted to show you that

1012
00:44:05,222 --> 00:44:06,123
because I guess it's fun.

1013
00:44:07,203 --> 00:44:08,984
It never saw the day of light,

1014
00:44:09,044 --> 00:44:12,325
so maybe in the next game we'll do a moon DLC.

1015
00:44:13,497 --> 00:44:14,857
All right, thank you.

1016
00:44:14,877 --> 00:44:17,919
So if you have any questions, then you can ask me.

1017
00:44:25,203 --> 00:44:26,043
Hi, thanks.

1018
00:44:26,284 --> 00:44:26,804
Great talk.

1019
00:44:26,824 --> 00:44:27,604
I love the game.

1020
00:44:28,205 --> 00:44:30,486
So sort of a bonus question first.

1021
00:44:30,626 --> 00:44:33,607
As a big fan of the genre, are we

1022
00:44:33,648 --> 00:44:36,209
going to see a sequel maybe in a different setting,

1023
00:44:36,249 --> 00:44:38,430
like World War something?

1024
00:44:40,125 --> 00:44:49,913
But the main question is sadly about the business part a little bit, as a gamer who was waiting for the revival of the genre.

1025
00:44:50,653 --> 00:44:57,359
Because it seemed to me, I was aware of the game since its announcement, because I was hoping for it.

1026
00:44:58,139 --> 00:45:03,405
It seemed like initially the game got very little visibility, maybe from the publisher as well,

1027
00:45:03,845 --> 00:45:09,111
and sort of after a while became this cult hit that people knew was very good,

1028
00:45:09,131 --> 00:45:13,835
that it started selling, that's what at least the Steam Spy data seemed to suggest.

1029
00:45:14,096 --> 00:45:17,539
The community kind of exploded, people started talking about it,

1030
00:45:17,599 --> 00:45:21,583
so if you can share anything about that part, that would be interesting.

1031
00:45:21,864 --> 00:45:26,868
Sure. So regarding the first part, we actually, it's a small anecdote but we have time,

1032
00:45:27,969 --> 00:45:33,233
we went to Barcelona to visit Pyro, or at least Gonzo, who was sort of the director of the first

1033
00:45:33,253 --> 00:45:37,437
Commandos games, and he played Shadow Tactics and he loved it very much and that was very important

1034
00:45:37,457 --> 00:45:41,500
to us and we were very happy about it. But the Commandos IP is a very difficult IP to get,

1035
00:45:41,721 --> 00:45:48,426
so that is most likely not going to happen. And regarding the second question, so yeah,

1036
00:45:50,193 --> 00:45:51,996
We don't really, we're not good at marketing,

1037
00:45:52,036 --> 00:45:54,140
and marketing is hard, and you need a lot of money

1038
00:45:54,200 --> 00:45:55,943
or clever ideas, I guess, to do that.

1039
00:45:56,003 --> 00:45:57,886
And we knew that the game was very good,

1040
00:45:58,247 --> 00:46:01,212
and for some reason it didn't get traction very much.

1041
00:46:01,272 --> 00:46:03,316
We had a very early trailer, but it wasn't very good.

1042
00:46:03,750 --> 00:46:05,231
So that didn't do much.

1043
00:46:05,271 --> 00:46:07,391
And I think the biggest marketing asset that we

1044
00:46:07,431 --> 00:46:08,472
actually had was the demo.

1045
00:46:08,692 --> 00:46:10,292
Like we said, there's a free demo of the game.

1046
00:46:10,592 --> 00:46:12,553
And we released that one or two weeks before the game.

1047
00:46:12,853 --> 00:46:14,573
And that's when it sort of started to kick in.

1048
00:46:14,633 --> 00:46:17,534
But then it's a game that takes a while to play, takes a

1049
00:46:17,574 --> 00:46:18,234
while to get into.

1050
00:46:18,294 --> 00:46:20,815
So press would also, they didn't really release reviews

1051
00:46:20,915 --> 00:46:23,095
on the first day because we didn't send it to them early

1052
00:46:23,135 --> 00:46:23,656
enough, I guess.

1053
00:46:24,116 --> 00:46:26,536
Plus, there was things like The Last Guardian coming out

1054
00:46:26,596 --> 00:46:28,777
that some people might have been waiting for, or Final

1055
00:46:28,817 --> 00:46:29,577
Fantasy XV.

1056
00:46:30,617 --> 00:46:31,138
Small games.

1057
00:46:32,058 --> 00:46:32,298
They don't.

1058
00:46:32,665 --> 00:46:34,706
directly fight with our game, but still.

1059
00:46:35,486 --> 00:46:37,667
And so I guess that word to mouth was basically

1060
00:46:37,707 --> 00:46:38,787
the main thing that helped us then.

1061
00:46:38,847 --> 00:46:40,988
The game was good and then people talked about it.

1062
00:46:41,268 --> 00:46:42,549
You could always tell your friend that,

1063
00:46:42,589 --> 00:46:43,649
hey, there's a free demo, right?

1064
00:46:43,709 --> 00:46:45,690
You just, you don't have to buy it just because I tell you.

1065
00:46:45,710 --> 00:46:47,451
You can always get the demo and you can start playing.

1066
00:46:47,991 --> 00:46:50,872
And I think this is the biggest, best thing we did

1067
00:46:50,912 --> 00:46:53,213
for marketing that probably helped elevate the game

1068
00:46:53,674 --> 00:46:54,974
in the second and in the long run,

1069
00:46:55,134 --> 00:46:56,775
because they could just play it and you can try it.

1070
00:46:58,115 --> 00:46:59,236
One tip regarding demos.

1071
00:46:59,336 --> 00:47:00,376
If you're doing a demo for PS4,

1072
00:47:02,213 --> 00:47:04,094
be sure that it's a demo and not a trial.

1073
00:47:04,274 --> 00:47:06,434
They have this weird thing where if you make your game

1074
00:47:06,474 --> 00:47:08,775
and you can basically upgrade the game to the full version,

1075
00:47:08,835 --> 00:47:09,916
which we thought was pretty cool,

1076
00:47:09,936 --> 00:47:11,496
then you don't have to download it again or whatever.

1077
00:47:11,837 --> 00:47:15,058
It's a trial and it will not be visible in the demo section.

1078
00:47:15,398 --> 00:47:16,979
It will actually not be visible anywhere.

1079
00:47:17,359 --> 00:47:19,279
So don't do that.

1080
00:47:20,720 --> 00:47:23,221
Make it a demo, which might suck, but yeah.

1081
00:47:24,121 --> 00:47:24,281
Thanks.

1082
00:47:27,177 --> 00:47:36,803
So I lived in Japan for over 15 years and because of that I tend to be a little bit allergic to things, media, that portrays Japan from in the West, right?

1083
00:47:37,984 --> 00:47:44,468
And I've been really impressed with the game including like the voiceovers and all that and so I'm wondering how is it you got it so right?

1084
00:47:44,528 --> 00:47:48,010
I mean do you have somebody from Japan on the team or how did you do that?

1085
00:47:48,295 --> 00:47:49,916
Yeah, that was a big, big process.

1086
00:47:49,936 --> 00:47:51,756
We did not have anyone from Japan on the team,

1087
00:47:51,856 --> 00:47:54,717
but we had someone who studies Japanese culture from Munich.

1088
00:47:54,737 --> 00:47:56,418
We had him come over and check out the game

1089
00:47:56,958 --> 00:47:59,319
and give us mostly feedback on stuff

1090
00:47:59,359 --> 00:48:04,220
like the way they talk to each other or visual stuff,

1091
00:48:04,260 --> 00:48:05,561
like how much stone did they use

1092
00:48:05,581 --> 00:48:06,501
when they built their houses.

1093
00:48:06,541 --> 00:48:07,821
And we did a lot of research into that.

1094
00:48:08,062 --> 00:48:10,682
And it's not that easy because like it's way back

1095
00:48:10,742 --> 00:48:11,743
and then it's also Japan.

1096
00:48:11,783 --> 00:48:13,003
So you don't find as much here,

1097
00:48:13,643 --> 00:48:15,044
but we try to do a lot there.

1098
00:48:15,304 --> 00:48:15,884
One of the biggest.

1099
00:48:16,494 --> 00:48:20,641
topics of discussion we had for a long, long time was if wagons had two or four wheels

1100
00:48:20,962 --> 00:48:23,346
back then and how that was an ongoing thing.

1101
00:48:26,048 --> 00:48:28,490
Yeah, this is the level of detail you get down to at some point.

1102
00:48:29,450 --> 00:48:33,494
Yeah, it was tough and I'm glad that you say that we did it well,

1103
00:48:33,534 --> 00:48:34,514
because you never really know.

1104
00:48:34,935 --> 00:48:38,818
Because if you ask a Japanese person, they will tell you yes, but maybe not.

1105
00:48:39,558 --> 00:48:40,479
Because they're very polite.

1106
00:48:40,899 --> 00:48:44,102
And we are actually releasing it in Japan as well now,

1107
00:48:44,122 --> 00:48:47,804
so we're hoping to get some more feedback there regarding that topic.

1108
00:48:52,042 --> 00:48:57,746
So, great game, I think I'll finish it one day since it's pretty big, but hypothetically,

1109
00:48:57,926 --> 00:49:05,492
if you were to do a sequel, how would you handle the number of characters?

1110
00:49:05,592 --> 00:49:10,756
Because right now it seems that the number of characters is quite good for the challenges

1111
00:49:10,796 --> 00:49:16,221
that you have, and it seems that if you added new characters, you would have to add specific

1112
00:49:16,281 --> 00:49:19,563
challenges just for that new character to the formula.

1113
00:49:19,623 --> 00:49:19,763
So...

1114
00:49:20,928 --> 00:49:24,271
In what way would you look into expanding the features of the game,

1115
00:49:24,331 --> 00:49:28,334
like where it would be environment, enemy focused, or actually character focused?

1116
00:49:29,055 --> 00:49:32,178
So, we like the number of five characters,

1117
00:49:32,498 --> 00:49:35,380
so we will be sticking to five characters for our next game as well.

1118
00:49:36,781 --> 00:49:39,584
We are actually developing a game that is like Shadow Tactics right now,

1119
00:49:39,664 --> 00:49:44,948
so this is not a secret yet, but it's not Shadow Tactics 2 though.

1120
00:49:47,622 --> 00:49:52,464
It is a very difficult topic for us to see how we want to change the thing up and how we want to keep it that way

1121
00:49:52,524 --> 00:49:55,065
because we don't want to take away too much from what made the game great.

1122
00:49:55,445 --> 00:49:59,447
We also don't want it to feel like a simple copy-paste thing, and that is very hard to do.

1123
00:49:59,927 --> 00:50:05,870
So our current approach is that we have characters that are similar to the Shadow Tactics characters

1124
00:50:05,910 --> 00:50:09,552
and we have characters that are completely new, but it's still five characters.

1125
00:50:09,592 --> 00:50:12,513
So we had to take some of the stuff out that we had in Shadow Tactics.

1126
00:50:14,554 --> 00:50:17,176
We also try to do stuff with the environment, as you said.

1127
00:50:17,256 --> 00:50:19,758
This is, I can't really talk about the feature yet,

1128
00:50:19,778 --> 00:50:20,438
but it's pretty cool.

1129
00:50:20,939 --> 00:50:22,780
It's about how you navigate environment

1130
00:50:22,860 --> 00:50:26,022
and make the maps feel more real, like real places.

1131
00:50:26,223 --> 00:50:28,584
This was a big thing that we're trying to focus on

1132
00:50:28,804 --> 00:50:29,385
in the next one.

1133
00:50:30,786 --> 00:50:31,286
Hope it works.

1134
00:50:32,527 --> 00:50:32,747
Yeah.

1135
00:50:33,808 --> 00:50:34,208
Anyone else?

1136
00:50:36,490 --> 00:50:36,670
Yes.

1137
00:50:40,893 --> 00:50:41,734
Awesome talk, thanks.

1138
00:50:42,074 --> 00:50:42,294
Thanks.

1139
00:50:42,554 --> 00:50:43,335
Oh, that sounded weird.

1140
00:50:44,797 --> 00:50:46,098
I have two questions if that's cool.

1141
00:50:47,318 --> 00:50:50,600
One, so swimming seems extremely powerful.

1142
00:50:50,640 --> 00:50:52,280
Like, what are the sort of conversations

1143
00:50:52,400 --> 00:50:53,861
that led to it being that way?

1144
00:50:54,681 --> 00:50:57,142
Well, we had in the beginning, we had systems

1145
00:50:57,182 --> 00:50:58,263
where you could hold your breath

1146
00:50:58,383 --> 00:50:59,663
only for a certain amount of time.

1147
00:51:00,003 --> 00:51:02,764
And then we realized that this was very complicated

1148
00:51:02,804 --> 00:51:04,905
and weird because we had to make behavior

1149
00:51:04,945 --> 00:51:06,426
for the guards shooting into the water

1150
00:51:06,546 --> 00:51:08,247
and what they would do if they see you in the water

1151
00:51:08,287 --> 00:51:09,727
because they can't really react to that.

1152
00:51:10,222 --> 00:51:12,683
And then we decided, well, we just use the small things,

1153
00:51:13,043 --> 00:51:17,225
the straw things to bamboo for the ninjas

1154
00:51:17,245 --> 00:51:17,945
to breathe underwater.

1155
00:51:17,965 --> 00:51:21,107
It's very ninja and very cool, and just have infinite thing.

1156
00:51:21,147 --> 00:51:23,448
And the water is powerful, but we

1157
00:51:23,548 --> 00:51:25,169
try to use it clever and level design.

1158
00:51:25,229 --> 00:51:27,510
So we know that you can always get away through the water,

1159
00:51:27,550 --> 00:51:29,130
but it's balanced in a way that you will usually

1160
00:51:29,170 --> 00:51:31,251
take one hit from a guard before you get into the water.

1161
00:51:31,591 --> 00:51:33,652
So this was sort of a way of balancing that.

1162
00:51:36,054 --> 00:51:37,714
And secondly, what were the triggers

1163
00:51:38,977 --> 00:51:40,237
determine when the music changes?

1164
00:51:43,118 --> 00:51:47,559
Well, it's just rather simple environment triggers that we place in the environment

1165
00:51:47,679 --> 00:51:52,361
or level events when we say, okay, you have killed two of the four guards you have to

1166
00:51:52,381 --> 00:51:54,421
kill and we are adding new layers to the system.

1167
00:51:54,722 --> 00:51:57,342
We actually have some pretty cool audio stuff going on in the game.

1168
00:51:57,562 --> 00:52:01,524
For example, if you perform an action, like the tracks are very basic, but if you perform

1169
00:52:01,544 --> 00:52:04,665
an action with one of the characters, each of them has an instrument attached to them.

1170
00:52:05,076 --> 00:52:06,537
And if you sort of do something with Moogan,

1171
00:52:06,557 --> 00:52:09,038
you will have these Kodo drums playing something.

1172
00:52:09,779 --> 00:52:11,760
Whatever it is, if you do something with Hayato,

1173
00:52:11,780 --> 00:52:12,760
I don't know what his instrument is.

1174
00:52:12,980 --> 00:52:14,261
Yuki is a flute, obviously.

1175
00:52:14,361 --> 00:52:17,363
So you sort of, nobody realizes that it's in the game,

1176
00:52:17,403 --> 00:52:18,683
but you're sort of building the soundtrack

1177
00:52:18,703 --> 00:52:21,565
by playing the game through these stingers that we have.

1178
00:52:22,005 --> 00:52:24,687
And yeah, the audio guy, Philippu,

1179
00:52:24,707 --> 00:52:26,128
he's, shout out to Philippu, he's great.

1180
00:52:26,328 --> 00:52:27,548
And he did a great job on it, I think.

1181
00:52:27,969 --> 00:52:28,229
Thanks.

1182
00:52:28,549 --> 00:52:28,829
Thank you.

1183
00:52:30,170 --> 00:52:30,430
Okay.

1184
00:52:32,031 --> 00:52:32,391
Any more?

1185
00:52:32,811 --> 00:52:32,971
No.

1186
00:52:34,252 --> 00:52:34,432
Cool.

1187
00:52:34,914 --> 00:52:40,605
then thanks so much for coming out and think of doing the rating thing. This is my first

1188
00:52:40,645 --> 00:52:44,433
talk at GDC. I would be very happy if you guys rated. Thank you.

